data.description: STUNNING GORGEOUS NEW KITCHEN with HEATED POOL on a CUL DE SAC in the highly-desired East Linden Estates where all the lots are oversized and the homes are custom large homes!! Move-in ready, well-maintained, loved and very clean, this home offers 3 bedrooms + 2.5 bathrooms + 2 car garage + stone fireplace + INCREDIBLE OUTDOOR LIVING SPACE completely screened and includes a heated pool with in-water seating and table, large brick pavered deck, TWO large covered lanai areas with TVs and an outdoor kitchen and kegerator + hot tub + large fenced yard for your family and pets!! You will want to just live outside enjoying the beautiful weather, entertaining your friends and family, or relaxing with your coffee and book or watching the games on TV while the family is swimming or playing in the yard!! This home is LARGE with almost 3,000 sq ft of living space; 3821 total! High ceilings, large windows and sliders, and an open floor plan make this home feel light, bright, and cheery! The remodeled, upgraded, GORGEOUS round designer kitchen with granite countertops is the CENTERPIECE of this home - it looks like something out of a magazine!! The kitchen offers new upgraded stainless steel appliances, range hood, real wood cabinets and floating shelves, under-mount sink, designer faucets and lighting, with a stunning round granite breakfast bar so everyone can see and talk to each other while sitting down! The kitchen is open to the large family room with stone fireplace, large glass sliders overlooking the lanai and pool area! Open up the sliders combining the indoor and outdoor living space and and you have a party home for entertaining!! There is room for everyone with a large living room/game room + family room + dinette area + formal dining room + a LARGE remodeled laundry room with new real wood cabinets to give you additional storage space (it even has outlets in the cabinets to charge your things!)! Newer washer and dryer included! Split floor plan offers complete privacy for the master suite! The master suite is spacious with an ensuite bathroom that is as large as a bedroom itself and has pool access, large soaking tub, walk-in shower, dual sinks, separate vanity area, and a LARGE walk-in closet!! The home is impressive just driving up to it with the GRAND entrance home at the end of the cul de sac! Landscaped with great curb appeal! Located close to groceries, shopping, restaurants, the hospital (which was just purchased by Tampa General Hospital), the Suncoat Parkway for quick and easy access to Tampa for work and play (35 minutes to Tampa International Airport! 1 hour + to TOP US BEACHES! 20 minutes to the sunset at Pine Island; fishing, swimming, boating, kayaking the clear Week Wachee River, seeing the manatees, dolphins...everything is so close! Roof 2008, TWO NEW AC UNITS in 2020. Call today to come see this immaculate home!
